<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="394" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[826,1429,311,1212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese et Trouessart" authorityYear="1889" box="[989,1113,311,335]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[989,1113,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Halolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was created by 
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese A. &amp; Trouessart E." pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="121 - 143" refId="ref4881" refString="Berlese A., Trouessart E. 1889 - Diagnoses d'Acariens nouveaux oupeuconnus - Bull. Bibl. Scient. Ouest, 2: 121 - 143." type="journal article" year="1889">Berlese and Trouessart (1889)</bibRefCitation>
, and later complimented by succeeding authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Hirschmann W." box="[1032,1244,381,405]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="21 - 24" refId="ref5824" refString="Hirschmann W. 1966 - Die Gattung Halolaelaps Berlese &amp; Trouessart 1889 nov. comb - Acarologie, 9: 21 - 24." type="journal article" year="1966">Hirschmann 1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans G. O. &amp; Till W. M." pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="139 - 270" refId="ref5608" refString="Evans G. O., Till W. M. 1979 - Mesostigmatic mites of Britain and Ireland (Chelicerata: Acari- Parasitiformes). An introduction to their external morphology and classification - Trans. Zool. Soc. Lond., 35: 139 - 270. doi: 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1979. tb 00059. x" type="journal article" year="1979">Evans and Till 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bregetova N. G. &amp; Shcherbak G. I." box="[900,1280,416,440]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="256 - 307" refId="ref5127" refString="Bregetova N. G., Shcherbak G. I. 1977 - Fam. Rhodacaridae - In: Gilyarov M. S., Bregetova N. G. (Eds) A Key to the Soil-Inhabiting Mites of the Mesostigmata - Nauka, Leningrad, p. 256 - 307. [In Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1977">
<taxonomicName authority="(Eds)" authorityName="Gwiazdowicz &amp; Teodorowicz" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Eds" box="[900,1018,416,440]" genus="Bregetova" pageId="2" pageNumber="406" rank="genus" status="N.G.">Bregetova</taxonomicName>
and Shcherbak 1977
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Karg W." box="[1299,1425,416,440]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="523" refId="ref5870" refString="Karg W. 1993 - Acari (Acarina), Milben Parasitiformes (Anactinochaeta), Cohors Gamasina Leach. Raubmilben - Die Tierwelt Deutschlands, 59 Teil. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Jena, pp. 523." type="journal article" year="1993">Karg 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Halliday R. B." box="[826,998,451,475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="214 - 230" refId="ref5783" refString="Halliday R. B. 2008 - Two new species of littoral mites from Australia (Acari: Halolaelapidae) - Syst. Appl. Acarol., 13: 214 - 230. doi: 10.11158 / saa. 13.3.8" type="journal article" year="2008">Halliday 2008</bibRefCitation>
). A typical character of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese et Trouessart" authorityYear="1889" box="[1305,1429,451,475]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1305,1429,451,475]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Halolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are two subequal dorsal shields, the idiosoma lacking horn-like caudal processes. The opisthonotal shield of many species bears a median incision running posteriorly from an anterior boarder towards the inner area of the shield. Dorsal setae commonly are simple or pilose. Tritosternum biflagellate with columnar base. Sternal shield subrectangular, fused with a presternal plate but not with endopodal plates, bearing three pairs of simple setae (st1-3) and two pairs of lyrifissures (iv1- 2). Pair of st4 setae situated in a soft membrane or on the metasternal plates and pair st5 on a trapezoidal genital shield. Peritremes either short or long and peritrematal shields not expanded posteriorly; ventrianal shield broad, bearing 3-4 pairs of ventral setae or reduced to anal shield with three circumanal setae; metapodal plates varied in shape; palp genu with 6 setae, palp apotele 3-tined, corniculi horn-like. Chelicerae chelate-dentate; movable digit without excrescences. Tectum with a median prong either evenly trifurcate or denticulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[826,1429,1240,1370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Tarsus I with claws; trochanter I with 6 setae; femur I with 13 setae; genu I with 12 setae; tibia I with 11 setae; genu III with 9 setae; coxae sometimes with spines.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="395" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[826,1429,1398,1949]" lastBlockId="3.[159,762,311,370]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="395" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">
Remarks — A division of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese et Trouessart" authorityYear="1889" box="[1305,1429,1398,1422]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1305,1429,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Halolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blaszak C. &amp; Ehrnsberger R." box="[991,1356,1434,1458]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="143 - 267" refId="ref4909" refString="Blaszak C., Ehrnsberger R. 1993 - Beitrage zur Kenntnis von Halolaelaps (Saprogamasellus) Gotz, 1952 (Acari: Gamasida: Halolaelapidae) - Genus, 4: 143 - 267." type="journal article" year="1993">Błaszak and Ehrnsberger (1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Blaszak C. &amp; Ehrnsberger R." box="[1369,1425,1433,1457]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="25 - 94" refId="ref4945" refString="Blaszak C., Ehrnsberger R. 1995 - Beitrage zur Kenntnis von Halolaelaps (Halogamasellus) subgen. nov., (Acari: Gamasida: Halolaelapidae) - Osnab. Nat. Mit., 20 / 21: 25 - 94." type="journal article" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Blaszak C. &amp; Ehrnsberger R." box="[826,896,1469,1493]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="159 - 181" refId="ref4990" refString="Blaszak C., Ehrnsberger R. 1998 a - Beitrage zur Kenntnis von Halolaelaps (Halolaelaps s. str.), (Acari: Gamasida: Halolaelapidae) - Osnab. Nat. Mit., 24: 159 - 181." type="journal article" year="1998">1998a</bibRefCitation>
,b) into 4 subgenera (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese et Trouessart" authorityYear="1889" box="[1144,1268,1469,1493]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1144,1268,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Halolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1275,1330,1469,1492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Halogamasellus</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gwiazdowicz &amp; Teodorowicz, 2017" authorityName="Gwiazdowicz &amp; Teodorowicz" authorityYear="2017" box="[940,1045,1504,1528]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Haloseius">
<emphasis box="[940,1045,1504,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Haloseius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1066,1246,1504,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Saprogamasellus</emphasis>
) based on the shape of epistome, the number of setae on femur I, and a spine on coxa II. Those designations and the characters used raised some multiple questions and controversies. For instance, why a type-species for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese et Trouessart" authorityYear="1889" box="[870,994,1679,1703]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[870,994,1679,1703]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Halolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that is 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brady" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[1098,1322,1679,1703]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marinus">
<emphasis box="[1098,1322,1679,1703]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Halolaelaps marinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has not been placed into the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese et Trouessart" authorityYear="1889" box="[1193,1317,1714,1738]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1193,1317,1714,1738]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Halolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1325,1378,1715,1738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but into subgenus 
<emphasis box="[1006,1176,1749,1773]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">Hologamasellus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Blaszak C. &amp; Ehrnsberger R." pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="25 - 94" refId="ref4945" refString="Blaszak C., Ehrnsberger R. 1995 - Beitrage zur Kenntnis von Halolaelaps (Halogamasellus) subgen. nov., (Acari: Gamasida: Halolaelapidae) - Osnab. Nat. Mit., 20 / 21: 25 - 94." type="journal article" year="1995">Błaszak and Ehrnsberger 1995</bibRefCitation>
) or why a 
<typeStatus box="[1103,1155,1785,1809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394">type</typeStatus>
species have not been designated for the four subgenera that had been erected. All the controversial issues on this subject have been presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Halliday R. B." box="[1150,1332,1889,1914]" pageId="2" pageNumber="394" pagination="214 - 230" refId="ref5783" refString="Halliday R. B. 2008 - Two new species of littoral mites from Australia (Acari: Halolaelapidae) - Syst. Appl. Acarol., 13: 214 - 230. doi: 10.11158 / saa. 13.3.8" type="journal article" year="2008">Halliday (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, and the authors of this paper agree with them completely. Therefore the discussion here does not follow the division of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese et Trouessart" authorityYear="1889" box="[291,415,346,370]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[291,415,346,370]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="395">Halolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into four subgenera.
</paragraph>
